Steps:

1. Make sure python, mysql server and mysql workbench is installed on system
2. Create a folder and open it in vscode.
3. Pull the project from 'https://github.com/subham-codes/TeachersPortal.git' and open main folder (where manage.py is present).

4. Create virtual environment and install the dependencies from requirements.txt
5. Create one database named 'student_listing' and in setting.py update databse credential accordingly
6. Open terminal in vscode and run migration commands:
    -> python manage.py makemigrations
    -> python manage.py makemigrate

7. Create superuser to access admin panel of django:
    -> python manage.py createsuperuser

8. Run the server using:
    -> python manage.py runserver

9. Open the link --> http://127.0.0.1:8000/ on browser
10. Login page will display -> Click Register now and insert credential and register -> login with created username and password.

11. Home page will appear and You can now add records by clicking 'Add data'.

12. Also records can be edit and delete by clicking edit and delete button.

13. Search functionality is present via student name. Add search value and click search button.

14. If more recods are present, pagination functionality is added at bottom of the table.

15. Logger file is also there to debug the code. This will have basic info for the running code.